News and features

Calm Before the Storm: A celebration of the RNLI at Poole Museum

Poole Museum is hosting a unique photography project celebrating the distinguished past and present of the RNLI.

Would you be able to foster a child for Poole?

Foster carers come from all types of backgrounds, so your income, ethnicity, gender, age and working patterns are not usually barriers.

Help for local residents who are at risk of eviction

The council's housing early prevention service offers free advice and support for residents in Poole and Bournemouth.

More news

Services and information

Benefits and financial help

Includes Council Tax support, housing benefit, change of circumstances and disability benefits.

Bins, waste and recycling

Includes information about when your bin day is, garden waste, black and blue bins and Poole tip.

Births, deaths and marriages

Includes registration, weddings, citizenship and funeral service diary.

Business and consumers

Includes licensing, business rates, trading standards and starting a business.

Children and families

Includes Family Information Directory, child care, fostering and adoption.

Community advice and safety

Includes antisocial behaviour, hate crime, emergencies and abuse.

Council and democracy

Includes find your Councillor, the Mayor, elections and voting and consultations.

Council Tax

Includes pay your Council Tax, change of circumstance and Council Tax bands.

Environmental problems

Includes graffiti, dog fouling, noise, pests and food safety.

Housing

Includes joining the housing register, finding a home, device and landlord support.

Jobs, training and volunteering

Includes applying for a job, apprenticeships and volunteering.

Libraries, museums, art and culture

Includes renewing a library book, your local library, Poole Museum and events.

Parking

Includes car parks, pay parking fine and parking permits.

Planning and Building Control

Includes find a planning application, applying for planning permission and applying for building regulations.

Schools and education

Includes school admissions, schools in Poole, holiday dates and adult education.

Social care and health

Includes adults and older people, carers, children and family care.

Sports and leisure

Includes beaches, sports centres, tennis courts and parks.

Streets and travel

Includes roadworks, bridges, bus passes and public toilets.
